## 3. Deploying with GitHub Pages
**Situation:** After building my portfolio locally and pushing the code to GitHub, the final step was to transform it from a repository into a live, accessible website.
**Goal:** My goal was to deploy the project via GitHub Pages, ensuring that all Markdown files rendered correctly as a cohesive, functional site.
**Action:** I navigated through the repository settings to configure the GitHub Pages source to my `main` branch.
I managed the deployment process using Git Bash, which involved resolving path issues for images and the mock interview video to ensure everything
loaded correctly on the live site.
**Outcome:** The portfolio was successfully published at a live URL, which I then submitted via Blackboard.
This task confirmed my ability to manage the full lifecycle of a software project, from local development and version control to final cloud deployment.
